198template <class T>
199class Local {
200 public:
201 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
202 template <class S>
203 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
204 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
210 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
211 }
212
216 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
217
221 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
222
223 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
224
225 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
226
237 template <class S>
238 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
239 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
240 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
241 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
242 if (b == nullptr) return false;
243 return *a == *b;
244 }
245
246 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
247 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
248 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
249 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
250 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
251 if (b == nullptr) return false;
252 return *a == *b;
253 }
254
265 template <class S>
266 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
267 return !operator==(that);
268 }
269
270 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
271 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
272 return !operator==(that);
273 }
274
280 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
281#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
282 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
283 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
284 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
285#endif
286 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
287 }
288
294 template <class S>
295 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
296 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
297 }
298
304 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
305 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
306 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
307 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
308 const BasicTracedReference<T>& that);
309
310 private:
311 friend class TracedReferenceBase;
312 friend class Utils;
313 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
314 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
315 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
316 template<class F> friend class Local;
317 template <class F>
318 friend class MaybeLocal;
319 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
320 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
321 friend class String;
322 friend class Object;
323 friend class Context;
324 friend class Isolate;
325 friend class Private;
326 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
327 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
328 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
329 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
330 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
331 friend class HandleScope;
332 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
333 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
334 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
335 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
336 template <class F>
337 friend class ReturnValue;
338 template <class F>
339 friend class Traced;
340 template <class F>
341 friend class TracedGlobal;
342 template <class F>
343 friend class BasicTracedReference;
344 template <class F>
345 friend class TracedReference;
346
347 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
348 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
349 T* val_;
350};

370template <class T>
371class MaybeLocal {

373 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
374 template <class S>
375 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
376 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
377 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
378 }
379
380 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
381
386 template <class S>
387 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
388 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
389 return !IsEmpty();
390 }
391
396 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
397
402 template <class S>
403 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
404 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
405 }
406
407 private:
408 T* val_;
409};

432static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
433static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
434
435template <typename T>
436class WeakCallbackInfo {
437 public:
438 using Callback = void (*)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
439
440 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
441 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
442 Callback* callback)
443 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
444 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
445 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
446 }
447 }
448
449 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
450 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
451 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
452
453 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
454 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
455 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
456 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
457 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
458 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
459 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
460
461 private:
462 Isolate* isolate_;
463 T* parameter_;
464 Callback* callback_;
465 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
466};
467
468
469// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
470// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
471// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
472// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
473// possible to request a second pass callback.
474enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
475
489template <class T> class PersistentBase {
490 public:
495 V8_INLINE void Reset();
500 template <class S>
501 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
502
507 template <class S>
508 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
509
510 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
511 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
512
513 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
514 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
515 }
516
517 template <class S>
518 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
519 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
520 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
521 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
522 if (b == nullptr) return false;
523 return *a == *b;
524 }
525
526 template <class S>
527 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
528 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
529 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
530 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
531 if (b == nullptr) return false;
532 return *a == *b;
533 }
534
535 template <class S>
536 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
537 return !operator==(that);
538 }
539
540 template <class S>
541 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
542 return !operator==(that);
543 }
544
557 template <typename P>
558 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
559 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
560 WeakCallbackType type);
561
569 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
570
571 template<typename P>
572 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
573
574 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
575 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
576
583 V8_INLINE void AnnotateStrongRetainer(const char* label);
584
586 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
587
591 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
592
597 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
598
599 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
600 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
601
602 private:
603 friend class Isolate;
604 friend class Utils;
605 template<class F> friend class Local;
606 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
607 template <class F>
608 friend class Global;
609 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
610 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
611 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
612 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
613 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
614 friend class Object;
615
616 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
617 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
618
619 T* val_;
620};

667template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
668 public:
672 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
678 template <class S>
679 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
680 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
681 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
682 }
688 template <class S, class M2>
689 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
690 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
691 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
692 }
699 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
700 Copy(that);
701 }
702 template <class S, class M2>
703 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
704 Copy(that);
705 }
706 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
707 Copy(that);
708 return *this;
709 }
710 template <class S, class M2>
711 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
712 Copy(that);
713 return *this;
714 }
720 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
721 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
722 }
723
724 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
725 template <class S>
726 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
727#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
728 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
729 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
730 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
731#endif
732 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
733 }
734
735 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
736 template <class S>
737 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
738 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
739 }
740
741 private:
742 friend class Isolate;
743 friend class Utils;
744 template<class F> friend class Local;
745 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
746 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
747
748 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
749 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
750 template<class S, class M2>
751 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
752};

833class TracedReferenceBase {
834 public:
839 bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
840
845 V8_INLINE void Reset();
846
850 V8_INLINE v8::Local<v8::Value> Get(v8::Isolate* isolate) const;
851
856 bool IsEmptyThreadSafe() const {
857 return this->GetSlotThreadSafe() == nullptr;
858 }
859
863 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
864
869 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
870
871 protected:
875 void SetSlotThreadSafe(void* new_val) {
876 reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<void*>*>(&val_)->store(
877 new_val, std::memory_order_relaxed);
878 }
879
883 const void* GetSlotThreadSafe() const {
884 return reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<const void*> const*>(&val_)->load(
885 std::memory_order_relaxed);
886 }
887
888 // val_ points to a GlobalHandles node.
889 internal::Address* val_ = nullptr;
890
891 friend class internal::BasicTracedReferenceExtractor;
892 template <typename F>
893 friend class Local;
894 template <typename U>
895 friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&, const Local<U>&);
896 friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&,
897 const TracedReferenceBase&);
898};

1164 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1165
1169 template <class S>
1170 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1171
1176 template <class S>
1177 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1178
1179 template <class S>
1180 V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1181 return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1182 const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1183 }
1184};

1394class ScriptOriginOptions {
1395 public:
1396 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1397 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1398 bool is_module = false)
1399 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1400 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1401 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1402 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1403 : flags_(flags &
1404 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1405
1406 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1407 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1408 }
1409 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1410 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1411 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1412
1413 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1414
1415 private:
1416 enum {
1417 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1418 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1419 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1420 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1421 };
1422 const int flags_;
1423};

1800class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1801 public:
1809 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1810 enum BufferPolicy {
1811 BufferNotOwned,
1812 BufferOwned
1813 };
1814
1815 CachedData()
1816 : data(nullptr),
1817 length(0),
1818 rejected(false),
1819 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1820
1821 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1822 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1823 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1824 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1825 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1826 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1827 ~CachedData();
1828 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1829 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1830 const uint8_t* data;
1831 int length;
1832 bool rejected;
1833 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1834
1835 // Prevent copying.
1836 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1837 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1838 };
1839
1843 class Source {
1844 public:
1845 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1846 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1847 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1848 V8_INLINE explicit Source(Local<String> source_string,
1849 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1850 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1851
1852 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1853 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1854 // alive.
1855 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1856
1857 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1858
1859 // Prevent copying.
1860 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1861 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1862
1863 private:
1864 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1865
1866 Local<String> source_string;
1867
1868 // Origin information
1869 Local<Value> resource_name;
1870 int resource_line_offset;
1871 int resource_column_offset;
1872 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1873 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1874 Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options;
1875
1876 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1877 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1878 // set when calling a compile method.
1879 CachedData* cached_data;
1880 };

2409 ~RegisterState();
2410 RegisterState(const RegisterState& other);
2411 RegisterState& operator=(const RegisterState& other);
2412
2413 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
2414 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
2415 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
2416 void* lr; // Link register (or nullptr on platforms without a link register).
2417 // Callee saved registers (or null if no callee saved registers were stored)
2418 std::unique_ptr<CalleeSavedRegisters> callee_saved;
2419};

2423 size_t frames_count; // Number of frames collected.
2424 StateTag vm_state; // Current VM state.
2425 void* external_callback_entry; // External callback address if VM is
2426 // executing an external callback.
2427 void* top_context; // Incumbent native context address.
2428};

3971 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3972 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3973 //
3974 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.

4496template<typename T>
4497class ReturnValue {
4498 public:
4499 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4500 : value_(that.value_) {
4501 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
4502 }
4503 // Local setters
4504 template <typename S>
4505 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4506 template <typename S>
4507 V8_INLINE void Set(const BasicTracedReference<S>& handle);
4508 template <typename S>
4509 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4510 // Fast primitive setters
4511 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4512 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4513 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4514 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4515 // Fast JS primitive setters
4516 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4517 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4518 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4519 // Convenience getter for Isolate
4520 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4521
4522 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4523 template <typename S>
4524 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4525
4526 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4527 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4528 // value.
4529 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4530
4531 private:
4532 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4533 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4534 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4535 template <class F, class G, class H>
4536 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4537 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4538 V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4539 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4540 internal::Address* value_;
4541};

6648struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
6649 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6650 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
6651 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
6652 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query,
6653 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
6654 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
6655 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
6656 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
6657 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6658 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6659 : getter(getter),
6660 setter(setter),
6661 query(query),
6662 deleter(deleter),
6663 enumerator(enumerator),
6664 definer(definer),
6665 descriptor(descriptor),
6666 data(data),
6667 flags(flags) {}
6668
6669 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6671 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter = nullptr,
6672 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter = nullptr,
6673 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query = nullptr,
6674 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = nullptr,
6675 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = nullptr,
6676 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),

7777struct JitCodeEvent {
7778 enum EventType {
7779 CODE_ADDED,
7780 CODE_MOVED,
7781 CODE_REMOVED,
7782 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7783 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7784 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7785 };
7786 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7787 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7788 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7789 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7790 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7791 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7792
7793 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7794 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7795 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7796 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7797 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7798 // function.
7799 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7800
7801 // Type of event.
7802 EventType type;
7803 CodeType code_type;
7804 // Start of the instructions.
7805 void* code_start;
7806 // Size of the instructions.
7807 size_t code_len;
7808 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7809 Local<UnboundScript> script;
7810 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7811 // code line information which is returned from the
7812 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7813 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7814 void* user_data;
7815
7816 struct name_t {
7817 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7818 // zero-terminated.
7819 const char* str;
7820 // Number of chars in str.
7821 size_t len;
7822 };
7823
7824 struct line_info_t {
7825 // PC offset
7826 size_t offset;
7827 // Code position
7828 size_t pos;
7829 // The position type.
7830 PositionType position_type;
7831 };
7832
7833 struct wasm_source_info_t {
7834 // Source file name.
7835 const char* filename;
7836 // Length of filename.
7837 size_t filename_size;
7838 // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7839 // source file.
7840 const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7841 // Number of entries in the line number table.
7842 size_t line_number_table_size;
7843 };
7844
7845 wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7846
7847 union {
7848 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7849 struct name_t name;
7850
7851 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7852 struct line_info_t line_info;
7853
7854 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7855 void* new_code_start;
7856 };
7857
7858 Isolate* isolate;
7859};
7860
7866enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7867 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7868 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7869 // Throughput may be throttled.
7870 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7871 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7872 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7873 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7874 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7875 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7876 // in this mode.
7877 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7878 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7879 // turn off latency optimizations.
7880 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7881};

7889 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
7890};

10061template <class T>
10062class Maybe {
10063 public:
10064 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
10065 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
10066
10070 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
10071
10076 V8_INLINE void Check() const {
10077 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10078 }
10079
10084 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
10085 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
10086 return IsJust();
10087 }
10088
10093 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
10094 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10095 return value_;
10096 }
10097
10102 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
10103 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
10104 }
10105
10106 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10107 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
10108 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
10109 }
10110
10111 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10112 return !operator==(other);
10113 }
10114
10115 private:
10116 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
10117 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
10118
10119 bool has_value_;
10120 T value_;
10121
10122 template <class U>
10123 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10124 template <class U>
10125 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
10126};
10127
10128template <class T>
10129inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
10130 return Maybe<T>();
10131}
10132
10133template <class T>
10134inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
10135 return Maybe<T>(t);
10136}
10137
10138// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
10139template <>
10140class Maybe<void> {
10141 public:
10142 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
10143 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
10144
10145 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10146 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
10147 }
10148
10149 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10150 return !operator==(other);
10151 }
10152
10153 private:
10154 struct JustTag {};
10155
10156 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
10157 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
10158
10159 bool is_valid_;
10160
10161 template <class U>
10162 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10163 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
10164};
10165
10166inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10825template <class T>
10826Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that) {
10827 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10828}
10829
10830template <class T>
10831Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<T>& that) {
10832 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10833}
10834
10835template <class T>
10836Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const BasicTracedReference<T>& that) {
10837 return New(isolate, *that);
10838}
10839
10840template <class T>
10841Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10842 if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10843 T* that_ptr = that;
10844 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10845 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10846 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10847}
10848
10849
10850template<class T>
10851template<class S>
10852void Eternal<T>::Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) {
10853 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10854 val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10855 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));
10856}
10857
10858template <class T>
10859Local<T> Eternal<T>::Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
10860 // The eternal handle will never go away, so as with the roots, we don't even
10861 // need to open a handle.
10862 return Local<T>(val_);
10863}
10864
10865
10866template <class T>
10867Local<T> MaybeLocal<T>::ToLocalChecked() {
10868 if (V8_UNLIKELY(val_ == nullptr)) V8::ToLocalEmpty();
10869 return Local<T>(val_);
10870}
10871
10872
10873template <class T>
10874void* WeakCallbackInfo<T>::GetInternalField(int index) const {
10875#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10876 if (index < 0 || index >= kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback) {
10877 V8::InternalFieldOutOfBounds(index);
10878 }
10879#endif
10880 return embedder_fields_[index];
10881}
10882
10883
10884template <class T>
10885T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10886 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
10887 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
10888 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10889 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
10890 p));
10891}
10892
10893
10894template <class T, class M>
10895template <class S, class M2>
10896void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
10897 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10898 this->Reset();
10899 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10900 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10901 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10902 M::Copy(that, this);
10903}
10904
10905template <class T>
10906bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
10907 using I = internal::Internals;
10908 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
10909 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
10910 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
10911}

10915void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
10916 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
10917 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_));
10918 val_ = nullptr;
10919}

10943template <class T>

10945V8_INLINE void PersistentBase<T>::SetWeak(
10946 P* parameter, typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
10947 WeakCallbackType type) {
10948 using Callback = WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback;
10949#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
10950#pragma GCC diagnostic push
10951#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wcast-function-type"
10952#endif
10953 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter,
10954 reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
10955#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
10956#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
10957#endif
10958}

10997template <class T>
10998Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
10999 if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
11000 V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
11001 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11002 other.val_ = nullptr;
11003 }
11004}
11005
11006template <class T>
11007template <class S>
11008Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
11009 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11010 if (this != &rhs) {
11011 this->Reset();
11012 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
11013 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
11014 V8::MoveGlobalReference(
11015 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
11016 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11017 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
11018 }
11019 }
11020 return *this;
11021}

11023template <class T>
11024internal::Address* BasicTracedReference<T>::New(
11025 Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot, DestructionMode destruction_mode) {
11026 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
11027 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
11028 return V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
11029 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
11030 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
11031 destruction_mode == kWithDestructor);
11032}
11033
11034void TracedReferenceBase::Reset() {
11035 if (IsEmpty()) return;
11036 V8::DisposeTracedGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_));
11037 SetSlotThreadSafe(nullptr);
11038}

11040v8::Local<v8::Value> TracedReferenceBase::Get(v8::Isolate* isolate) const {
11041 if (IsEmpty()) return Local<Value>();
11042 return Local<Value>::New(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(val_));
11043}

11045V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11046 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11047 v8::internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(lhs.val_);
11048 v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(rhs.val_);
11049 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
11050 if (b == nullptr) return false;
11051 return *a == *b;
11052}
11053
11054template <typename U>
11055V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11056 const v8::Local<U>& rhs) {
11057 v8::internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(lhs.val_);
11058 v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(*rhs);
11059 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
11060 if (b == nullptr) return false;
11061 return *a == *b;
11062}

11064template <typename U>
11065V8_INLINE bool operator==(const v8::Local<U>& lhs,
11066 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11067 return rhs == lhs;
11068}

11070V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11071 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11072 return !(lhs == rhs);
11073}

11077 const v8::Local<U>& rhs) {
11078 return !(lhs == rhs);
11079}
11080
11081template <typename U>
11082V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const v8::Local<U>& lhs,
11083 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11084 return !(rhs == lhs);
11085}

11249 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Number>::value, "type check");
11250 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11251}
11252
11253template<typename T>
11254void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
11255 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11256 using I = internal::Internals;
11257 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
11258 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
11259 return;
11260 }
11261 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11262}
11263
11264template<typename T>
11265void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11266 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11267 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11268 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11269 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11270 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11271 return;
11272 }
11273 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11274}
11275
11276template<typename T>
11277void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11278 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Boolean>::value, "type check");
11279 using I = internal::Internals;
11280 int root_index;
11281 if (value) {
11282 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11283 } else {
11284 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11285 }
11286 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11287}
11288
11289template<typename T>
11290void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
11291 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11292 using I = internal::Internals;
11293 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11294}
11295
11296template<typename T>
11297void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
11298 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11299 using I = internal::Internals;
11300 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
11301}

11303template<typename T>
11304void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
11305 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, String>::value, "type check");
11306 using I = internal::Internals;
11307 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11308}

11310template <typename T>
11311Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11312 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11313 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11314}
11315
11316template <typename T>
11317Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11318 using I = internal::Internals;
11319 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11320 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11321 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11322}

11328}

11333 return value_[-1];

11537
11538Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11539#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11540 using A = internal::Address;
11541 using I = internal::Internals;
11542 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11543 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11544 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11545 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11546 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11547 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11548 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11549 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11550 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11551#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11552 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11553 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11554 value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11555#endif
11556 internal::Isolate* isolate =
11557 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11558 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11559 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11560 }
11561#endif
11562 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11563}
11564
11565
11566void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11567#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11568 using A = internal::Address;
11569 using I = internal::Internals;
11570 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11571 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11572 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11573 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11574 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11575 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11576 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11577 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11578#ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
11579 offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
11580#endif
11581 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11582 A value = I::ReadExternalPointerField(
11583 isolate, obj, offset, internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag);
11584 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
11585 }
11586#endif
11587 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11588}

11606String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11607 using A = internal::Address;
11608 using I = internal::Internals;
11609 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11610
11611 ExternalStringResource* result;
11612 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11613 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11614 A value =
11615 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11616 internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11617 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11618 } else {
11619 result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11620 }
11621#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11622 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11623#endif
11624 return result;
11625}

11628String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11629 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11630 using A = internal::Address;
11631 using I = internal::Internals;
11632 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11633 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11634 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11635 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11636 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11637 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11638 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11639 A value =
11640 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11641 internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11642 resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11643 } else {
11644 resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11645 }
11646#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11647 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11648#endif
11649 return resource;
11650}

12183Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
12184#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12185 using A = internal::Address;
12186 using I = internal::Internals;
12187 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12188 A embedder_data =
12189 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12190 int value_offset =
12191 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12192 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
12193#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
12194 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
12195 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
12196 value =
12197 I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
12198#endif
12199 internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
12200 *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
12201 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
12202 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
12203#else
12204 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
12205#endif
12206}

12209void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
12210#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12211 using A = internal::Address;
12212 using I = internal::Internals;
12213 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12214 A embedder_data =
12215 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12216 int value_offset =
12217 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12218#ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
12219 value_offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
12220#endif
12221 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(ctx);
12222 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(
12223 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, embedder_data, value_offset,
12224 internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag));
12225#else
12226 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
12227#endif
12228}
